'''Ambrose Rayappan''' (25 February 1901 – 24 November 1999) was the tenth and the first indigenous Archbishop of the [[Archdiocese of Pondicherry and Cuddalore]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Our Bishops|url=http://www.pondicherryarchdiocese.org/archdiocese.php?link_id=1|publisher=Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Pondicherry and Cuddalore|accessdate=5 December 2014}}</ref> He was born at [[Dharapuram]], Tamil Nadu. He was ordained as a priest for the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Coimbatore|Diocese of Coimbatore]] on 16 December 1923. He participated in the Second Vatican council as a ''Council Father''.<ref name='ch'>{{Catholic-hierarchy|bishop|bray|Archbishop Ambrose Rayappan|5 December 2014}}</ref>

On 8 January 1953 he was appointed auxiliary bishop of Pondicherry and Cuddalore, and was consecrated on 25 March 1953 by [[Auguste-Siméon Colas]]. He was appointed as coadjutor of the same archdiocese on 7 August 1953. When Mgr. Colas resigned, he succeeded him on 28 November 1955. He resigned his post on 17 March 1973. He was succeeded by [[Venmani S. Selvanather]].

