The '''Christian Church in French Polynesia''' was formed in 1958 when a single [[parish]] left the [[Maói Protestant Church]]. It was motivated by a political issue, this church supported the independence from [[France]], while the Maói Protestant Church was against. There's no [[theological]] differences between these churches. In 2004 there were 8 congregations and 1,000 members.<ref>{{cite web|author=Johannes a Lasco Library |url=http://www.reformiert-online.net/adressen/detail.php?id=12193&lg=eng |title=Address data base of Reformed churches and institutions |website=Reformiert-online.net |date=2004-02-20 |accessdate=2016-03-03}}</ref>
