The presence of '''Islam in [[Guam]]''' is quite small, centered on the island's only [[mosque]], the Masjid Al-Noor in [[Mangilao]]. Muslims in Guam are from a wide variety of backgrounds, both originating in traditionally [[Muslim countries]], as well as [[Chamorro people|Chamorro]] converts and mainland [[American people|American]]s.<ref>Leo Babauta, ' Muslim Association of Guam', referenced June 27, 2010, © 2009 Guampedia, URL: http://guampedia.com/muslim-association-of-guam/</ref>

