{{refimprove|date=January 2017}}
'''Islamic radio''' is a category of [[radio format]]s that focus on [[Religious broadcasting|transmitting programming]] with a [[Islam]]ic message.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Marsden|first1=Magnus|title=Articulating Islam: Anthropological Approaches to Muslim Worlds|date=2012|page=92}}</ref> Radio stations can be [[Public broadcasting|public]], [[Commercial broadcasting|private]] and [[non-profit]] (or some form of [[Community radio]]).
These radio stations typically focus on [[Islam]]ic [[religious programming]], such as reading of the [[Quran]], [[talk radio]]-style programming (sometimes including live radio call-in shows) and/or long-form "preaching and teaching" programs with [[news radio|news]] programming with associated topics that can have an economic or a political angle to [[Muslim community]]. In recent years during Ramadan, many UK cities with Muslim populations have set up [[Radio Ramadan]] stations that operate exclusively during Ramadan. These stations feature a variety of broadcasts including [[Qira'at|Quran recitation]] and Islamic music known as [[Nasheeds]]
Many secular radio stations devote some of their weekend programming to religious programming; for example, during [[Friday prayers]] or [[Eid Mubarak]], [[Ramadan]].
==See also== * [[Islam]] * [[Christian radio]]
