'''Rahimahullah''' ({{lang-en|'''Allah have mercy upon him'''}}, {{lang-ar|''' رحمه الله'''}}) is a phrase often used after mentioning the [[Righteousness|righteous]] [[Islam]]ic personalities who came after the [[Sahabah|companions of Muhammad]].  The mention of a late [[teacher]], [[Scholarly method|scholar]], [[Leadership|leader]], or even a dear [[Kinship|relative]] who was known for his goodness can be followed by the [[Prayer|praying]] of [[mercy]] upon him.

