'''Strala yoga''' is a modern form of [[yoga]] that was founded in 2008 by [[Tara Stiles]].

==History==
The New York City Strala studio was founded by Tara Stiles and her husband Michael Taylor in 2008. The name stems from the Swedish word "stråla" meaning radiate light. The yoga style was first introduced on the YouTube channel belonging to Stiles. Strala has partner studios in Seattle, Singapore and Barcelona, and classes are offered in 20 countries around the world. Partner Gyms that offer Strala are CMG in Paris (30 clubs) and SCLA in the US. Strala has a few thousand Guides leading classes in various studios and clubs globally. Strala is now offered in 20 other countries.

== About ==   
Strala focuses on an overall concept of moving with ease. Natural movement, eastern influences of tai chi and shiatsu, and a positive, easy-going atmosphere are elements in Strala.<ref>{{cite web|title=Strala is the movement system that ignites freedom.|url=http://stralayoga.com/about/|website=Stralayoga|accessdate=6 May 2015}}</ref> Strala teachers are called "guides".<ref>{{cite web|title=Q&A with Strala Founder Tara Stiles|url=http://www.yogajournal.com/article/lifestyle/life-stiles/|website=Yoga Journal|accessdate=6 May 2015}}</ref>

